author: NOAH TRISTER
title: 4 moments that changed the 2015 baseball season
text:
LM Otero 4 moments that changed the 2015 baseball season 
Texas Rangers closer Shawn Tolleson throws during the ninth inning of a baseball game against the Los Angeles Angels in Arlington, Texas, Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015. (AP Photo/LM Otero) Posted: Monday, October 5, 2015 3:13 am | Updated: 5:01 am, Mon Oct 5, 2015. 4 moments that changed the 2015 baseball season Associated Press | 0 comments 
It could have been one of the most memorable comebacks in Los Angeles Angels history, but instead it will go down as a mere footnote. 
When the Angels scored five runs in the ninth inning Saturday to beat the Texas Rangers 11-10, they kept themselves in the postseason race for another day and prevented Texas from clinching the AL West. Then on Sunday, Texas beat the Angels, wrapping up the division and ensuring that Houston, not Los Angeles, would end up with a wild card.
